ditions.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Local tropical monsoon climates herbalists, traditional medicine suppliers, Indian native plant nurseries. May be wild-harvested in some regions."}, {"name": "Black European Elderberry", "slug": "black-european-elderberry", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 1, "origin": "Europe, widely naturalized. Traditional variety.", "traits": "Shrub/small tree 3-6m. Dark green pinnate leaves. Large creamy-white flower clusters.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Heavy producer when established.", "growing_notes": "Not traditionally grown in lowland tropical monsoon climates. Better suited to cooler regions like Munnar, Wayanad (hill stations). Used mainly for medicinal purposes in Ayurvedic medicines where cultivated.", "availability": "Limited availability in tropical monsoon climates. May be sourced from hill station nurseries, specialized herb gardens, international suppliers."}, {"name": "American Black Elderberry (wild type)", "slug": "american-black-elderberry-wild-type", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 2, "origin": "Native to eastern North America, from Canada to Gulf Coast.", "traits": "Multi-stemmed shrub 1.8-3.6m tall. Adaptable to various soil types including wet soils.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good yields in suitable conditions.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Limited in tropical monsoon climates. May be available through international seed suppliers, specialty nurseries."}, {"name": "Adams 🏆 HEIRLOOM", "slug": "adams-heirloom", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "New York, USA, 1926. Historic selection.", "traits": "Vigorous upright shrub. Large white flower clusters.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High yields, early ripening.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "International suppliers only."}, {"name": "York 🏆 HEIRLOOM", "slug"